<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President’s Special Assistant</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in the
                                Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HWA2" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d62fn1">Channel of transmission not indicated.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-26">October 26, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Personal and secret from <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Harry
                                Hopkins</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">W. Averell
                                Harriman</persName>.</p>
                        <p>If meeting in Bosra [<hi rend="italic">Basra</hi>] agreed to President
                            confident that between ourselves and the British we can make proper
                            arrangements with Iran and Iraq relative to Russian troops.</p>
                        <p>Reports of the Conference are very encouraging although, naturally,
                            everyone here disappointed that personal conference seems difficult.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>